# UnifiedMCP Environment Variables
# This file is now for reference only - use .dev.vars for Cloudflare Workers local development

# =============================================================================
# GOOGLE OAUTH2 CONFIGURATION (REQUIRED)
# =============================================================================

# Google OAuth2 Client Credentials
# Get these from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret

# OAuth2 Redirect URI (must match Google Console configuration)
# For local development: http://localhost:8788/oauth/callback
# For production: https://your-worker.your-subdomain.workers.dev/oauth/callback
REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8788/oauth/callback

# =============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION  
# =============================================================================

# Environment (development/production)
NODE_ENV=development

# =============================================================================
# MICROSOFT 365 API CONFIGURATION (Phase 3 - Future)
# =============================================================================

# These will be added when we implement Microsoft 365 tools
# MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=your-microsoft-client-id
# MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=your-microsoft-client-secret
# MICROSOFT_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8788/oauth/microsoft/callback

# =============================================================================
# CLOUDFLARE CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================

# These may be needed for production deployment
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=your-cloudflare-account-id
# CLOUDFLARE_ZONE_ID=your-cloudflare-zone-id

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================

# 1. Create .dev.vars file: cp .dev.vars.example .dev.vars
# 2. Set up Google OAuth2 Application:
#    - Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#    - Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application)
#    - Add authorized redirect URI: http://localhost:8788/oauth/callback
#    - Copy Client ID and Client Secret to .dev.vars
# 3. Enable required APIs:
#    - Google Drive API
#    - Google OAuth2 API
# 4. Configure test users (if app is not published)
# 5. Run: wrangler dev

# Security Notes:
# - NEVER commit .dev.vars file to git (it's in .gitignore)
# - Use minimal required scopes only ('openid email profile')
# - Store production secrets in Cloudflare Workers environment variables
# - Rotate client secrets regularly